About the Festival
Travel back in time to the 16th Century at the 34th Annual Florida Renaissance Festival, coming to Quiet Waters Park.
February 7th, 2026 through March 29th, 2026.
Saturday’s & Sunday’s only from 10:00AM to Sunset!
Over 100 Artisans selling their wares. Over 100 Performers to entertain.
Come Be Welcome in our 16th century renaissance Village! Browse through our Enchanted Artisan Marketplace where over one hundred merchants demonstrate and sell their wares. Behold blown glass, hammered pewter, wooden toys, hand-tooled leather, weaponry, unique pottery, abundant clothing, and a wealth of other riches, including Festival Memorabilia! Applaud hundreds of performers, not only on our twelve unique stages but all around you!
You’ll meet sword fighters, minstrels, magicians, wenches, and more! “All the World’s a Stage” here in the Village of Kimmendale. Cheer for Heroic Knights, as they mount their noble steeds and charge with thunderous speed in exciting Jousts, thrice daily! Indulge in a feast of fine foods, fit for royalty! From giant turkey legs to soft cotton candy, we have everything in between! Savor delectable desserts without a second thought. Raise a tankard of cold ale or hard cider at our lively pubs, and toast the Royal Court. For those with a gentler palate, we also offer a selection of meads, wines, frozen cocktails, and other non-alcoholic options.
Challenge yourself with games of chance and skill, from axe throwing and archery to sword fighting! Tackle our Tomato Torture challenge with precision and accuracy or show off your basketball skills with Head Toss. For those looking for a bigger thrill, climb our towering rock wall, take a spin on our dizzying Crow’s Nest, or endure the ferocious barrel ride. Climb aboard the ‘World’s Largest Rocking Horse’ and view the many more rides and games we offer from the treetops! There is So Much to do!
Come Experience the Adventure that is the One and Only Florida Renaissance Festival! Huzzah!
